      "body": "Recipe: smooth-over-k\u0304 \u21d2 reduced is CLOSED; Stacks 00NP (regular local \u21d2 domain) EXISTS in-project \u2014 do not re-derive either.\n\n- **`RingTheory.CohenMacaulay.isDomain_of_regularLocal`** (`AuslanderBuchsbaum.lean`, public, axiom-clean): any Noetherian regular local ring is a domain. This is the full Stacks `00NP`; docstrings elsewhere calling it a \"Mathlib gap\" predate its closure. Companions: `regularLocal_quotient_isRegularLocal_of_notMemSq` (R/(x) regular of spanFinrank \u22121 for `x \u2208 \ud835\udd2a\u2216\ud835\udd2a\u00b2`), `matsumura_isRegular_of_linearIndependent_cotangent` (\u00a73.C, cotangent-independent \u21d2 regular sequence).\n- **Smooth over `Spec k\u0304` \u21d2 reduced**: `AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.isReduced_of_smooth_of_isAlgClosed` (`CodimOneExtension.lean` \u00a73.B Step B.f) + ring-level `isReduced_of_isStandardSmooth_of_isAlgClosed` (Step B.e). Proof pattern that works at *every* point (no 00OF needed): reduced is stalk-local (`isReduced_of_isReduced_stalk`) + detected at maximal localisations (`isReduced_ofLocalizationMaximal`), and B.d\u2032 closed-point regularity + 00NP give those. Contrast: stalk *regularity* at non-closed points stays 00OF-blocked.\n- Useful glue found in v4.31 Mathlib: `RingHom.isStandardSmooth_respectsIso` (`.2` = precompose ring equiv \u2014 transports a standard-smooth presentation across `gammaSpecField_ringEquiv` base identification), `RingHom.isStandardSmooth_algebraMap`, `isReduced_localizationPreserves`, `isReduced_of_noZeroDivisors`.\n- Mathlib does NOT have: smooth \u21d2 reduced/geometrically-reduced at scheme level (checked `Geometrically/Reduced.lean`, `Morphisms/Smooth.lean`, `RingTheory/Smooth/*`), nor regular-local \u21d2 domain (`RegularLocalRing/` has only `Defs.lean`). `Group/Smooth.lean` goes the other way (geom. reduced group scheme \u21d2 smooth).\n- Iteration trick: a root-level scratch `import Mathlib + import AlgebraicJacobian.Albanese.CodimOneExtension` type-checks in ~4 min against warm oleans; `open private <name> from <module>` lets `#print axioms` reach private decls.",
